title: Neuratron PhotoScore & NotateMe Ultimate 8.0.4
description:
PhotoScore & NotateMe Ultimate is the full-featured version of the PhotoScore & NotateMe Lite scanning software included with Sibelius. This powerful software can also scan music into other MIDI software, such as sequencers. You can even use it on its own to scan in, play back, transpose, and print scores, and even save audio files.

PhotoScore & NotateMe Ultimate reads printed and handwritten music or PDFs in secondsâ€”not just the notes, but also printed slurs, dynamics, lyrics, guitar tab, chord diagrams, and more. You can then edit or transpose the music, play it back, extract the parts, and printâ€”just as if you'd input it yourself.
PhotoScore & NotateMe Ultimate provides a variety of time-saving features, such as a "bad timing navigator" that makes it quick and easy to find and correct rhythmic errors. Thereâ€™s also a Find and Replace dialog that enables you to fix lots of identical errors (for example, in text) in a single operation.

System requirements:

Windows
IBM-compatible Pentium III (or equivalent AMD processor) or higher PC with at least 512 MB RAM
Windows Vista, 7, or 8
512 MB RAM (more recommended if scanning many small staves, photos, or graphics)
40 MB available hard disk space (more recommended)
Adobe Reader 6.0 or later for viewing PhotoScoreâ€™s PDF help
A scanner (connected to your computer via a USB, Printer or SCSI port) and installed TWAIN or WIA driver software
